{
  "stem": "4760.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then that started, my mother sent my brother to France.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I could hardly go to school without being prepared with a bag like they have today, those bags for the books to put in--",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, we had these already in Germany in 1933, '34.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when I went to school, I never put the bag on my shoulders, I always left it loose and put the wrapping from the shoulder wraps on my hand to be prepared to fight.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I always was ready to fight.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they would come down on the school, out-- out of the school, and they would call us [GERMAN] and all kinds of names and would pick on us and would sometimes hit us.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was always ready to hit them back and nobody could get close to me because I always swung my bag to-- to make sure that I don't get hurt.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I did get hurt badly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had a broken nose because of being hit with a stick at the one time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In school, after school, after school, yes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Uh-huh.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I have to go back a little bit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After my father passed away in 1924-- no-- it's in-- in August of '25, in August of '25, my-- my father passed away.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And actually, my mother supported us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But before my father passed away, there was a man in town who became our second father.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] His-- [CRYING] His name was [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Isi ?] Joseph.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they used to have the [INAUDIBLE], so he became from a very religious background because they-- they had to keep always kosher and everything else.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And also, my father and my second father, very close friends.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
